Step-by-Step Explanation
1. Models Folder
Student.cs → Represents the student entity with properties like Id, Name, USN.

StudentRegistration.cs → Represents the registration form model with validation attributes.

csharp
public class Student
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public string USN { get; set; }
}
csharp
public class StudentRegistration
{
    [Required]
    public string Name { get; set; }

    [Required]
    [StringLength(10)]
    public string USN { get; set; }

    [EmailAddress]
    public string Email { get; set; }
}
2. Controllers Folder
StudentController.cs → Handles requests, returns views, and demonstrates action results.

csharp
public class StudentController : Controller
{
    public IActionResult Index()
    {
        var students = new List<Student>
        {
            new Student { Id = 1, Name = "Alice", USN = "USN001" },
            new Student { Id = 2, Name = "Bob", USN = "USN002" }
        };
        return View(students);
    }

    public IActionResult Register() => View();

    [HttpPost]
    public IActionResult Register(StudentRegistration student)
    {
        if (ModelState.IsValid)
        {
            return RedirectToAction("Index");
        }
        return View(student);
    }

    public IActionResult ConfigDemo()
    {
        ViewBag.InstituteName = _config["StudentSettings:InstituteName"];
        return View();
    }
}
3. Views Folder
Index.cshtml → Displays student list in a table.

Register.cshtml → Registration form with validation.

ConfigDemo.cshtml → Displays configuration values.

Example Index.cshtml:

html
@model IEnumerable<StudentDemoApp.Models.Student>

<h2>Student List</h2>
<table>
    <tr><th>ID</th><th>Name</th><th>USN</th></tr>
    @foreach (var s in Model)
    {
        <tr>
            <td>@s.Id</td>
            <td>@s.Name</td>
            <td>@s.USN</td>
        </tr>
    }
</table>
4. wwwroot Folder
Contains static files like CSS, JS, images, and HTML.

Example: student-info.html → served directly via browser.

5. appsettings.json
Stores configuration values.

json
{
  "StudentSettings": {
    "InstituteName": "ABC Institute",
    "MaxStudents": 500
  }
}
6. Program.cs
Configures services, middleware, and routing.

csharp
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
builder.Services.AddControllersWithViews();

var app = builder.Build();
app.UseStaticFiles();
app.UseRouting();

app.MapControllerRoute(
    name: "default",
    pattern: "{controller=Student}/{action=Index}/{id?}");

app.Run();
